texts.html: The Corvette Racing C7.R takes a turn at the Rolex Monterey Motorsports Reunion in Monterey, California.  Chevy Racing
text: The Corvette Racing C7.R takes a turn at the Rolex Monterey Motorsports Reunion in Monterey, California.

texts.html: Chevrolet surprises with the racing version of the Corvette, which it showed off at the Rolex Monterey Motorsports Reunion in Monterey, Calif.(Photo: Chris Woodyard/USA TODAY)
MONTEREY, Calif. -- As if anyone had any doubt about a racing version of the new 2014 Chevrolet Corvette, the answer came Sunday at the Rolex Monterey Motorsports Reunion.
text: MONTEREY, Calif. -- As if anyone had any doubt about a racing version of the new 2014 Chevrolet Corvette, the answer came Sunday at the Rolex Monterey Motorsports Reunion.

texts.html: Without any prior warning to the hundreds of Corvette fans gathered here, what is expected to be the next racing Corvette -- clad in black-and-white camouflage -- took a lap at the Mazda Raceway Laguna Seca.
text: Without any prior warning to the hundreds of Corvette fans gathered here, what is expected to be the next racing Corvette -- clad in black-and-white camouflage -- took a lap at the Mazda Raceway Laguna Seca.

texts.html: It was supposed to be a "parade lap," but it seemed mighty fast. The Corvette, designated the C7.R, was driven hard around the track, apparently to signal that it intends to be a force like never before on the racing circuit. It's the seventh generation Corvette and the R stands for racing.
text: It was supposed to be a "parade lap," but it seemed mighty fast. The Corvette, designated the C7.R, was driven hard around the track, apparently to signal that it intends to be a force like never before on the racing circuit. It's the seventh generation Corvette and the R stands for racing.

texts.html: The lap comes days after the new seventh-generation Corvette made available for drives bythe press near here last week. The new car is more powerful and more capable than the one it replaces, and it has dramatic new styling. The styling stood out in particular when it came to the racing version of the Corvette.
text: The lap comes days after the new seventh-generation Corvette made available for drives bythe press near here last week. texts.html: Its first racing appearance won't come until January in Daytona Beach, Fla.
